<P><STRONG>October 6<BR><BR></STRONG>October brings a cool autumn breeze, beautiful fall foliage and of course more planning for the 2012 International CES!</P>
<P><STRONG>Social Media at the 2012 International CES <BR></STRONG>At this year’s 2012 CES, you’ll encounter an integrated social media experience! We encourage you to visit, follow, like, view and browse our social media platforms in order to get updates as they happen up to, during and following 2012 CES.<BR><BR>CES Social Media Platforms <BR>Contact: Ryan Emge <BR>Manager, Social Media Marketing <BR>703-907-7795 <BR><A href="mailto:remge@CE.org ">remge@CE.org <BR><BR></A>Use #CES to share your 2012 CES news. This also helps us identify you as a CES exhibitor in the social space.</P>
<P>Exhibitors are welcome, and encouraged, to submit a guest blog post(s) for our official blog: <A href="http://blog.ce.org" target=_blank>Digital Dialogue</A>. There are many ways to express yourself and company in a blog including words, photos and videos. Your blog post can feature your company, products and services but only in an informative way – no straight sales pitches, please! Share your knowledge and passion for technology, and let our readers know what you will be demonstrating at the 2012 International CES.</P>
<P>If you have specific announcements that support promoting CES and the industry, we encourage you to reach out to us early to see if there are any opportunities to cross-promote. Also, please make sure to specifically visit the social media portion of our Exhibitor PR Kit for example blog, Facebook and Twitter posts.</P>
<P><STRONG><IMG style="FLOAT: right" alt="" src="/images/content/190X136cnet.jpg">CNET’s Best of CES<BR></STRONG>CNET will continue to produce the&nbsp;<A href="http://cesweb.org/awards/bestOfCES.asp">Best of CES Awards</A> program for 2012. The CNET Best of CES awards name the most buzz-worthy, category-defining, innovative and promising products at the show. The competition is judged by CNET’s esteemed editorial team, published online to their widespread audience, and includes the coveted Best of Show and People’s Voice awards. No submission is necessary - but make sure CNET editors know what you'll be debuting at CES.</P>
<P><STRONG>CES Online Exhibitor Workshop&nbsp;<BR></STRONG><A href="http://cesweb.org/exhibitors/resources/exhibitor-workshop.asp">The Exhibitor Workshop series</A>is your one-stop shop for all things related to exhibiting at the 2012 International CES. We know that first-timers and veterans alike need some assistance navigating the various aspects of exhibiting at the world’s largest consumer technology tradeshow. <BR><BR>If you missed our webcast on how to Optimize Your Marketing Resources and Get the Most Press Coverage, don’t worry, it has been archived online. Up next, hear from GES and the CES operations team for tips and tricks on show planning and booth logistics: Register now for this FREE opportunity. </P>
<UL class=text>
<LI class=text><STRONG>Meet GES – Official Show Contractor</STRONG> October 11, 2011 – 2 p.m. EST <BR>A panel of GES experts will discuss shipping deadlines and rigging, booth design and maintenance, electrical issues, union jurisdictions and material handling, and anything else you need to know to ensure your materials reach the show efficiently. </LI>
<LI class=text><STRONG>CES Operations – Show Planning and Booth Logistics </STRONG>October 19, 2011 – 2 p.m. EST <BR>The CES Operations team will help make your booth planning easier with tips on navigating the show, securing hotel reservation, ordering booth services and setting up your booth within show guidelines. </LI></UL><STRONG>Regional Media Outreach Campaign <BR></STRONG>Each year, CES publicizes its exhibitors and their products and technologies to the media in their respective geographic regions. Take part in this free program. The regional releases are a great way to get your company’s news and intentions for the show publicized in your region’s top outlets in the weeks leading up to CES.<BR><BR>You can submit a short quote (75 words or less) about your company’s participation at CES to Allison Fried at <A href="mailto:afried@CE.org">afried@CE.org</A>. Each release will contain approximately four quotes and inclusion is first-come, first-serve. The deadline for inclusion is November 21, 2011.<BR><BR>The quote must be from a high-level executive involved with the show and highlight anything new and exciting your company plans to showcase, as well as why you think CES is important to your company’s success. When submitting a quote, make sure to include company name and headquarter location. <BR><BR>Sample Quote: "We look forward to participating in the 2012 International CES because it offers unparalleled business opportunities and is the very best venue to launch our new products," said John Doe, president and CEO of Exhibitor X, based in location Y. "This year we are showcasing our latest consumer technology product and announcing several key partnerships." <BR><BR>The releases will be distributed to the following regions in mid-December: <BR>
