<LI class=text>Free high-speed Internet service </LI>
<LI class=text>Use of pre-registered CES Unveiled@NY press list </LI></UL>For more information on Unveiled@NY, including tabletop and sponsorship opportunities, package pricing and discounts for Innovations honorees, please contact <A href="mailto:CESUnveiled@CE.org">CESUnveiled@CE.org</A>. 
<P><STRONG>CES Unveiled @ London <BR></STRONG>November 17, 2011 <BR>Inmarsat Conference Center <BR>London, United Kingdom</P>
<P>The Consumer Electronics Association is taking CES Unveiled internationally with the new <A href="http://cesweb.org/exhibitors/sponsorships/pressOpportunitites.asp">http://cesweb.org/exhibitors/sponsorships/pressOpportunitites.asp</A>. Don’t miss this opportunity to get your product in front of key UK media and analysts, just in time to make headlines before the holiday selling season. <BR><BR>The Western European CE market is expected to exceed $221 billion in 2011. Sign up today to jumpstart your CES success and promote your services and products to the dynamic UK and European marketplace.</P>
<P>Tabletop Exhibitors at CES Unveiled @ London receive: </P>
<UL class=text>
<LI class=text>Opportunity to network with key UK media and analysts </LI>
<LI class=text>Exclusive demonstrations and networking opportunities </LI>
<LI class=text>Extensive pre-event promotion of all event exhibitors and sponsors to CES’ UK and European media list </LI>
<LI class=text>A 6-foot draped exhibit table </LI>
<LI class=text>Two exhibitor passes to the event </LI>
<LI class=text>55 cm x 71 cm pole sign with exhibitor name </LI>
<LI class=text>High-speed Internet access and 1,000 watts of electricity </LI></UL>
<P>Download the CES Unveiled @ London event brochure for more information. <BR>Contact <BR>Tira Gordon <BR>+ 1 703-907-4324 <BR>Email: <A href="mailto:tgordon@CE.org">tgordon@CE.org</A><STRONG><BR><BR>Follow Me, The Official Mobile App for CES <IMG style="FLOAT: left" alt="" src="/images/content/2012CES-QR-FM.gif"><BR></STRONG>Follow Me, the official mobile app for CES, is a great pre-show planning and on-site navigational tool. If you have a web based smartphone, you can build your schedule an<IMG style="FLOAT: right" alt="" src="/images/content/FollowMe.jpg">d plan your time at CES on the go – anywhere, anytime! <BR><BR>Create your show schedule on Follow Me and sync it to your MyCES account or vice versa. With Follow Me you can search the exhibitor directory for companies or products you want to see, add them to your show agenda and even share your agenda with your friends. You can also get important show alerts, late-breaking CES news, view real-time interactive floor maps when they’re available and so much more! <BR><BR>Scan this code with your smartphone to download the official 2012 CES mobile app now! Or point your mobile browser to <A href="http://m.core-apps.com/2012CES" target=_blank>http://m.core-apps.com/2012CES</A><BR><BR><STRONG>Schedule Your Exhibitor Press Conference <BR></STRONG>All CES exhibitors are eligible to hold a newsworthy press conference and have their event included on the official CES press event list. Events can be held in a CES-provided press conference room in either the Venetian or the LVCC, the exhibitor’s booth or in an exhibitor’s paid meeting room. Reservations generally run in two-hour increments and come with a standard room set including theater-style seating for up to 200; three draped tables; a stage riser, a podium with a light and a wired microphone and two easels for signage. Exhibitor press conference options are as follows:</P>
<UL class=text>
<LI class=text><STRONG>Monday, January 9, 2012 – Press Day Power Sessions </STRONG></LI>
<LI>Due to exhibitor demand for expanded Press Day offerings, new for 2012, CES will offer complimentary one hour Press Day room reservations for companies looking to break their news quickly and directly to CES media. Venetian Ballroom D (4,911 sq. ft) will be reserved for the Press Day Power Sessions, and exhibitors will be given 15 minutes for set-up, 30 minutes for the event and 15 minutes for tear down. Press conference rooms will have a standard room set and exhibitors may not make ANY alterations to existing set. </LI>
<LI class=text><STRONG>Tuesday, January 10, 2012 – Opening Day <BR></STRONG>Press conferences or events may be held with written notification before, during or after show hours, with the exception of the opening CES Keynote timeslot, 8:30-10 a.m. on Tuesday, January 10. Events held on the show floor before or after show hours require advanced security forms and hired security guards. </LI>
<LI class=text><STRONG>Wednesday, January 11, 2012 – Day Two </STRONG>Press conferences or events may be held with written notification before, during or after show hours. However, events held on the show floor before or after show hours require advanced security forms and hired security guards.</LI></UL>To schedule a press event, please send your Press Conference Reservation Request form to Allison Fried at <A href="mailto:afried@CE.org">afried@CE.org</A>. <BR><BR><STRONG>CESweb for News<BR></STRONG>Make sure you bookmark <A href="http://www.CESweb.org">www.CESweb.org</A> for up to the minute news on the latest stories surrounding the 2012 International CES. You will find buzz-worthy topics posted front and center on the homepage, along with links to our blog, relevant videos and photos. We also have a news section with breaking headlines, such as our latest keynote announcements: 
